document_data.History:
Originally, the castle housed the hundreds of drow that comprised [[House Ch没mavh]] until the [[Silence of Lolth]] and the betrayal of the city's [[Archmage]] brought ruin to the drow city. The armies of [[Kurgoth Hellspawn]] attacked the city and, as the surviving loyalists of House Ch没mavh barred themselves inside Castle Maerimydra, the [[fire giant]]s, [[demon]]s, and [[goblinoid]]s besieged it.

However, on [[Elient 28]], [[1372 DR]], [[Irae T'sarran]], the leader of the cult of [[Kiaransalee]] in Maerimydra, gathered her followers to her and slaughtered the remaining [[Lolth]]-worshiping drow of House Ch没mavh and seized the castle for her own. This was much to the annoyance of the [[Jaezred Chaulssin]], who also plotted to seize control of the city.{{Cite web enhancement/City of Wyrmshadows|4}}

By [[Marpenoth 17]], Irae managed to summon the [[Undying Temple]] above Castle Maerimydra, which disrupted the [[Weave]] in a growing radius around the castle.
